						               													<description>Caravan is a card game invented in conjunction with the video game &amp;quot;Fallout: New Vegas&amp;quot; (released in October 2010).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is set in the post-apocalyptic world of the video game series, and players take the role of caravan owners delivering goods across the wasteland.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Caravan can be played by 2 players using 2 standard decks of playing cards, or the special deck included with the video game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Caravan plays a bit like a head-to-head version of Blackjack, with the objective being to build three sets of cards - or &amp;quot;caravans&amp;quot; - with the highest possible value. &amp;#10;You must is outbid your opponent's caravans, without being too light (under 21) or overburdened (over 26).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Certain cards - like Jacks, Queens or Kings - change the rules for building caravans, like the numerical order in which you are allowed to play cards onto your caravans.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Caravan plays in about 10-20 minutes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
